WEBVTT

00:00:14.000 --> 00:00:16.000
Narrator:
 THE AMERICAN FAMILY.

00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:18.000
IT'S SURE A LOT DIFFERENT
 THAN IT USED TO BE.

00:00:18.000 --> 00:00:21.000
I WOULDN'T SAY ANDY'S
THE MOST RESPONSIBLE FATHER,

00:00:21.000 --> 00:00:23.000
BUT HE'S FINE.

00:00:23.000 --> 00:00:25.000
Narrator:
 TODAY, A LOOK
 AT ONE MODERN FAMILY.

00:00:25.000 --> 00:00:28.000
Woman:
 THIS HOUSE THAT WE LIVE IN
 WAS ANDY'S HOUSE,

00:00:29.000 --> 00:00:31.000
AND THE BOYS
AND I FELT

00:00:31.000 --> 00:00:33.000
A LITTLE BIT LIKE
WE WERE GUESTS.

00:00:33.000 --> 00:00:36.000
I GET TO WATCH
A WRESTLING GAME KIND OF.

00:00:36.000 --> 00:00:38.000
Narrator:
 AND NEW INSIGHTS INTO WHAT
 IT MEANS TO BE A STEPPARENT.

00:00:38.000 --> 00:00:41.000
MY SORT OF RULE
OF THUMB, WHICH I GET
ENORMOUS HASSLE ABOUT,

00:00:41.000 --> 00:00:45.000
IS, AS A STEPPARENT,
YOU CAN BE A GOOD HOST
AND FRIEND, AND THAT'S IT.

00:00:45.000 --> 00:00:48.000
I THINK IT MAY BE
THAT YOU WISH SO MUCH

00:00:48.000 --> 00:00:49.000
YOU COULD GET CLOSE...

00:00:50.000 --> 00:00:52.000
Narrator:
 "BRAZELTON ON PARENTING."

00:01:12.000 --> 00:01:14.000
OVER THE LAST GENERATION,

00:01:14.000 --> 00:01:16.000
OUR DEFINITION
OF THE WORD "FAMILY"

00:01:16.000 --> 00:01:19.000
HAS CHANGED DRAMATICALLY.

00:01:19.000 --> 00:01:21.000
SURE, THERE'S STILL
THE TRADITIONAL NOTION

00:01:21.000 --> 00:01:23.000
OF MOM, DAD, AND THE KIDS,

00:01:23.000 --> 00:01:26.000
BUT OUR HIGH RATE
OF DIVORCE, FOR ONE,

00:01:26.000 --> 00:01:29.000
HAS TRANSFORMED THE STRUCTURE
OF THE FAMILY FOREVER.

00:01:30.000 --> 00:01:32.000
TODAY, WE'RE GOING TO
EXPLORE THE NEW FAMILY

00:01:32.000 --> 00:01:35.000
AND START BY LOOKING
THROUGH THE EYES OF PARENTS

00:01:36.000 --> 00:01:37.000
WHO'VE DISCOVERED
NEW MEANING

00:01:38.000 --> 00:01:40.000
TO THE PHRASE,
"HAPPILY EVER AFTER."

00:01:47.000 --> 00:01:50.000
Brazelton:
 A PORTRAIT OF OUR NEW FAMILY.

00:01:50.000 --> 00:01:53.000
THIS IS WHERE THEY LIVE,

00:01:53.000 --> 00:01:56.000
AND THIS IS
 WHAT THEY LOOK LIKE.

00:01:56.000 --> 00:01:58.000
JIMMY, AGE 12,

00:01:58.000 --> 00:02:01.000
LILLY, 11,

00:02:01.000 --> 00:02:03.000
BILLY, 9,

00:02:04.000 --> 00:02:07.000
TWINS SUMMER
 AND HANNAH, 8,

00:02:07.000 --> 00:02:09.000
HATTIE, 2 1/2.

00:02:11.000 --> 00:02:13.000
Boy:
 YOU GUYS, DO YOU
 WANT TO PLAY?

00:02:13.000 --> 00:02:16.000
THERE'S NOT A DAY
GOES BY THAT ANDY AND I
DON'T SAY TO EACH OTHER,

00:02:17.000 --> 00:02:19.000
"ARE WE THE LUCKIEST
PEOPLE IN THE WORLD?"

00:02:19.000 --> 00:02:21.000
Brazelton:
 NANCY AND ANDY,
 BOTH DIVORCED,

00:02:21.000 --> 00:02:24.000
ACTUALLY MET
 THROUGH THEIR KIDS
 ON A SKI TRIP.

00:02:24.000 --> 00:02:28.000
Nancy: HE WAS PULLING OUT
 RAW BROCCOLI FROM HIS
 BACKPACK AT A SKI LODGE.

00:02:28.000 --> 00:02:31.000
EVERYBODY WAS HAVING HOT
CHOCOLATE, AND HIS DAUGHTER'S
WERE EATING RAW BROCCOLI.

00:02:31.000 --> 00:02:34.000
Andy:
 THAT'S SORT OF
 HOW WE MET.

00:02:34.000 --> 00:02:36.000
( overlapping dialogue )

00:02:36.000 --> 00:02:38.000
Brazelton:
 THEIR FIRST DATE WAS,
 WELL, UNUSUAL.

00:02:38.000 --> 00:02:42.000
Nancy:
 WE WENT ON OUR FIRST DATE,
 AND HE ACTUALLY TOOK NOTES.

00:02:42.000 --> 00:02:44.000
I'VE GOT THESE CUTE
LITTLE GIRLS,

00:02:44.000 --> 00:02:47.000
AND I WANT TO MAKE
SURE THEY'RE GETTING
GOOD QUALITY CARE.

00:02:47.000 --> 00:02:49.000
I WAS A PRETTY TOUGH
INTERVIEWER.

00:02:49.000 --> 00:02:52.000
Brazelton:
 IT WAS A LITTLE MORE
 RELAXED FOR THE KIDS.

00:02:52.000 --> 00:02:54.000
Nancy:
 THEY'RE THE ONES WHO KNEW
 EACH OTHER FROM SCHOOL.

00:02:54.000 --> 00:02:56.000
IT WASN'T LIKE
 THEY WERE STRANGERS.

00:02:56.000 --> 00:02:58.000
Brazelton:
 THINGS PROGRESSED QUICKLY.

00:02:58.000 --> 00:03:00.000
Nancy:
 WE KNEW WE WERE
 GETTING MARRIED.

00:03:00.000 --> 00:03:03.000
THE KIDS THOUGHT WE
 WOULD GET MARRIED, TOO,

00:03:03.000 --> 00:03:05.000
BUT THEY WOULD SAY,
 "DON'T GET MARRIED."

00:03:05.000 --> 00:03:07.000
THE BOYS WOULD SAY
"I DON'T LIKE THE GIRLS,"

00:03:07.000 --> 00:03:09.000
AND THE GIRLS WOULD SAY,
"I DON'T LIKE THE BOYS."

00:03:09.000 --> 00:03:11.000
Andy:
 ONE MORNING, WE GOT THE TWO
 OLDEST, LILLY AND JIMMY,

00:03:11.000 --> 00:03:14.000
AND I JUST SAID,
 "I'M GOING TO TELL
 YOU TWO A SECRET.

00:03:14.000 --> 00:03:16.000
DON'T TELL THE LITTLE ONES.
WE'RE GETTING MARRIED."

00:03:16.000 --> 00:03:19.000
WE DIDN'T TELL THEM
 WE WERE GOING TO DO IT
 IN ABOUT 36 HOURS.

00:03:19.000 --> 00:03:22.000
AND THE KIDS ALL THOUGHT
IT WAS A LOT OF FUN.

00:03:22.000 --> 00:03:24.000
Brazelton:
 AND ONCE THE DUST SETTLED?

00:03:25.000 --> 00:03:26.000
Nancy:
 WE HEAR SOME FRIENDS
 TALK ABOUT

00:03:27.000 --> 00:03:29.000
THAT STEPSIBLINGS DON'T
 GET ALONG REAL WELL AND--

00:03:29.000 --> 00:03:32.000
Andy:
 THEY REALLY, YOU KNOW,
 DO SEEM TO GET ALONG.

00:03:32.000 --> 00:03:34.000
Nancy:
 THEY DO, AND HERE WE HAVE

00:03:34.000 --> 00:03:37.000
SOME NORMAL
 SIBLING RELATIONSHIPS

00:03:37.000 --> 00:03:39.000
WHERE IT'S REALLY

00:03:39.000 --> 00:03:41.000
THE BOYS DO
MOST OF THE FIGHTING,

00:03:41.000 --> 00:03:43.000
AND IT'S PRETTY MUCH
WITH EACH OTHER.

00:03:44.000 --> 00:03:45.000
ONCE IN A WHILE,
 THEY TEASE THE GIRLS,

00:03:46.000 --> 00:03:48.000
BUT THE GIRLS WILL TEASE
 THEM RIGHT BACK.

00:03:48.000 --> 00:03:50.000
Andy: AND THEN THE BABY,
 HATTIE, HAS REALLY BROUGHT
 EVERYONE TOGETHER.

00:03:51.000 --> 00:03:52.000
Nancy:
 SHE IS A GREAT JOY.

00:03:52.000 --> 00:03:55.000
I DIDN'T EXPECT
 TO BE DOING THIS
 AT 44 YEARS OLD.

00:03:55.000 --> 00:03:57.000
HATTIE WAS BORN
JUST FOUR MONTHS EARLY.

00:03:57.000 --> 00:03:59.000
SHE WAS ONLY
A POUND AND A HALF.

00:03:59.000 --> 00:04:03.000
Nancy:
 EVERYBODY JUST REALLY GATHERS
 AROUND THIS LITTLE KID,

00:04:03.000 --> 00:04:05.000
AND, YOU KNOW,

00:04:05.000 --> 00:04:07.000
SHE'S AN INTEGRAL PART
OF EVERYBODY'S LIFE,

00:04:07.000 --> 00:04:10.000
AND I THINK THAT SORT OF
MADE EVERYBODY FEEL CLOSER.

00:04:11.000 --> 00:04:13.000
THE BOYS--
 ONE OF THE NICER THINGS

00:04:13.000 --> 00:04:15.000
FOR ME
 WITH HAVING HATTIE

00:04:15.000 --> 00:04:18.000
IS SEEING SUCH A DIFFERENT
 SIDE TO THEM.

00:04:18.000 --> 00:04:20.000
IT'S ALL OF A SUDDEN
A VERY GENTLE,

00:04:20.000 --> 00:04:23.000
VERY NICE SIDE.

00:04:23.000 --> 00:04:25.000
Andy:
 THEY REFER TO EACH OTHER
 AS BROTHERS AND SISTERS.

00:04:25.000 --> 00:04:27.000
Nancy:
 WE NEVER HEAR "STEPBROTHER"
 OR "STEPSISTER."

00:04:27.000 --> 00:04:30.000
IT'S ALWAYS "MY SISTER,"
"MY BROTHER."

00:04:30.000 --> 00:04:32.000
AND, YOU KNOW,
THEY'LL TALK ABOUT,

00:04:32.000 --> 00:04:36.000
YOU KNOW,
ANDY IS THE STEPFATHER
AND I'M THE STEPMOTHER,

00:04:36.000 --> 00:04:39.000
BUT THEY TALK
ABOUT EACH OTHER
AS BROTHERS AND SISTERS.

00:04:39.000 --> 00:04:41.000
Brazelton:
 NANCY AND ANDY ARE
 SENSITIVE STEPPARENTS.

00:04:41.000 --> 00:04:43.000
ANYBODY CAN HAVE
A BOO-BOO.

00:04:43.000 --> 00:04:46.000
Nancy:
TO ME, THE BIGGEST CHALLENGE
IS WALKING THAT LINE

00:04:47.000 --> 00:04:49.000
WHERE YOU DON'T WANT TO
OVERSTEP YOUR BOUNDARIES,

00:04:49.000 --> 00:04:52.000
YOU KNOW,
WITH DISCIPLINE.

00:04:52.000 --> 00:04:55.000
WALK IT OFF.
YOU'RE DONE.
GOOD JOB, SUMMER.

00:04:55.000 --> 00:04:57.000
Nancy:
FORTUNATELY, YOU KNOW,
WITH THE GIRLS,

00:04:57.000 --> 00:04:59.000
THEY'RE
REALLY GOOD KIDS,

00:04:59.000 --> 00:05:01.000
I DON'T NEED TO
DISCIPLINE THEM.

00:05:01.000 --> 00:05:03.000
GOOD!  GOOD!
( laughs )

00:05:04.000 --> 00:05:06.000
Nancy:
 I DON'T WANT TO
 PUSH MYSELF,

00:05:06.000 --> 00:05:08.000
BECAUSE I KNOW
 THEY HAVE A MOTHER.

00:05:08.000 --> 00:05:11.000
I CHERISH ALL THOSE
MOMENTS WITH THEM.

00:05:11.000 --> 00:05:13.000
I CAN BE A FRIEND
 TO THEM, TOO.

00:05:13.000 --> 00:05:16.000
I THINK IT'S MAYBE
 NOT AS INTENSE

00:05:16.000 --> 00:05:18.000
AS A MOTHER-DAUGHTER
 RELATIONSHIP WOULD BE,

00:05:18.000 --> 00:05:20.000
BUT, YOU KNOW,
I LOVE THEM

00:05:20.000 --> 00:05:22.000
AND HOPE THAT
THEY LOVE ME.

00:05:22.000 --> 00:05:24.000
Andy:
 THE BOYS, THEY'VE GOT
 A GREAT DAD.

00:05:24.000 --> 00:05:27.000
I DON'T TAKE THE ACTIVE
ROLE WITH THE BOYS

00:05:27.000 --> 00:05:29.000
AS A FATHER FIGURE.

00:05:29.000 --> 00:05:32.000
I'M JUST A ROLE MODEL.
 THEY SEE A GUY THAT
 GETS UP EARLY,

00:05:33.000 --> 00:05:35.000
WORKS HARD, WORKS LATE.

00:05:35.000 --> 00:05:37.000
Nancy:
 ON THE WEEKENDS,
 WE'VE GOT TO DO THE CHORES

00:05:37.000 --> 00:05:39.000
BEFORE WE CAN
GO OUT AND PLAY.

00:05:39.000 --> 00:05:41.000
BUT WHEN WE PLAY,
WE PLAY.

00:05:41.000 --> 00:05:45.000
Brazelton:
 NOW HE'S GOT BOYS,
 AND SHE'S GOT DAUGHTERS--

00:05:45.000 --> 00:05:48.000
A DREAM, BUT CHAOS.

00:05:48.000 --> 00:05:50.000
TRYING TO GET
FIVE LUNCHES READY,

00:05:50.000 --> 00:05:52.000
WITH A BABY
IN THE BACKGROUND,

00:05:52.000 --> 00:05:54.000
AND, YOU KNOW,
BREAKFAST IN THE MORNING,

00:05:54.000 --> 00:05:56.000
AND MAKE SURE
 WE HAVE FIVE FRUITS

00:05:56.000 --> 00:05:59.000
AND VEGETABLES APIECE,
 YOU KNOW, FOR--

00:05:59.000 --> 00:06:01.000
THAT'S 35 PIECES
OF FRUIT A DAY.

00:06:01.000 --> 00:06:03.000
THAT'S A LOT OF FRUIT.

00:06:03.000 --> 00:06:06.000
COME ON, TROOPS.
WE'RE GOING FOR THE PICNIC.
LET'S ROLL.

00:06:06.000 --> 00:06:08.000
WHOO!

00:06:08.000 --> 00:06:10.000
Andy:
 WE'RE GOING TO GET
 EIGHT PEOPLE ON SEVEN BIKES,

00:06:10.000 --> 00:06:13.000
AND WE'RE GONNA GO
 FOR A THREE-MILE BIKE RIDE.

00:06:13.000 --> 00:06:17.000
AND HOPEFULLY
THE SALAMI WON'T FALL
OUT OF THE KNAPSACK,

00:06:17.000 --> 00:06:19.000
AND WE'RE LUCKY ENOUGH TO SAY
THAT'S THE CHALLENGE

00:06:19.000 --> 00:06:21.000
THAT WE HAVE FOR THE DAY.

00:06:21.000 --> 00:06:24.000
Brazelton:
 THERE IT IS AGAIN--
 THEY FEEL LUCKY.

00:06:24.000 --> 00:06:27.000
Andy:
 WE'RE THE KIND OF--
 THE HALF-FULL GLASS.

00:06:27.000 --> 00:06:30.000
Nancy:
 WE BOTH LOOK AT THINGS
 AS THE GLASS IS HALF-FULL.

00:06:30.000 --> 00:06:33.000
I THINK IF I HAD STOPPED
 TO THINK MAYBE ABOUT

00:06:33.000 --> 00:06:35.000
ALL THE PROBLEMS,
 THINGS THAT COULD HAPPEN,

00:06:36.000 --> 00:06:38.000
MAYBE IT WOULD
HAVE GIVEN PAUSE,
BUT I DON'T THINK SO.

00:06:39.000 --> 00:06:40.000
I MEAN,
THE JOY I HAVE,

00:06:41.000 --> 00:06:43.000
BEING WITH HIM,

00:06:43.000 --> 00:06:46.000
IS WORTH ANY TRIAL
AND TRIBULATION.

00:06:46.000 --> 00:06:48.000
( singing )

00:06:48.000 --> 00:06:51.000
Nancy:
 I DON'T LOOK AT THEM
 AS "MY BOYS"

00:06:51.000 --> 00:06:53.000
AND THEN "HIS GIRLS."

00:06:53.000 --> 00:06:55.000
I LOOK AT THEM
 AS "OUR CHILDREN."

00:06:55.000 --> 00:06:57.000
Brazelton:
 IT ALL COMES TOGETHER

00:06:57.000 --> 00:06:59.000
WHEN THEY ALL
 COME TOGETHER.

00:06:59.000 --> 00:07:02.000
SITTING AROUND
THE DINING ROOM TABLE
IS ONE OF MY FAVORITES--

00:07:02.000 --> 00:07:04.000
WHEN WE'VE GOT
ALL THE KIDS THERE.

00:07:04.000 --> 00:07:08.000
JUST WATCHING THEM
SO ANIMATED AND HAVING
A GOOD TIME,

00:07:08.000 --> 00:07:10.000
AND SHARING THEIR DAY.

00:07:10.000 --> 00:07:12.000
AND THEY'VE GOT,
 YOU KNOW, SO MANY PEOPLE

00:07:12.000 --> 00:07:14.000
THAT THEY CAN PICK
 AND CHOOSE FROM,

00:07:14.000 --> 00:07:16.000
WHO THEY WANT TO
 SHARE SOMETHING WITH.

00:07:16.000 --> 00:07:18.000
Nancy:
 HERE WE GO...

00:07:18.000 --> 00:07:21.000
Andy:
 I JUST LOVE NANCY--
 WHEN I COME HOME FROM WORK,

00:07:21.000 --> 00:07:23.000
THAT THE MEALS
 THAT SHE HAS PREPARED--

00:07:23.000 --> 00:07:25.000
TO ME, THAT JUST
SAYS IT ALL.

00:07:25.000 --> 00:07:28.000
AND I JUST LOVE
A BIG DINING ROOM TABLE
FILLED WITH... EVERYONE.

00:07:28.000 --> 00:07:31.000
TO ME, THAT'S
THE NAME OF THE GAME.

00:07:31.000 --> 00:07:33.000
JUST SHARING YOUR LIFE.

00:07:33.000 --> 00:07:36.000
I'D BE VERY LONELY
IF I DIDN'T HAVE ANDY,

00:07:36.000 --> 00:07:39.000
IF I DIDN'T HAVE
THE KIDS.

00:07:39.000 --> 00:07:41.000
IT'S MY PLEASURE
TO INTRODUCE

00:07:41.000 --> 00:07:43.000
THE DANCING
GRANT GIRLS.

00:07:43.000 --> 00:07:45.000
LEADING THE WAY
IS SUMMER GRANT.

00:07:45.000 --> 00:07:47.000
WOULD YOU PLEASE
COME UP, SUMMER GRANT?
FOLLOWED BY...

00:07:47.000 --> 00:07:49.000
Brazelton:
 WHAT MAKES THE NEW
 FAMILY WORK?

00:07:49.000 --> 00:07:52.000
- IT'S THE SAME OLD THING.
- I'LL TAKE BABY HATTIE GRANT.

00:07:52.000 --> 00:07:55.000
Nancy:
 I THINK OUR FAMILY IS SPECIAL

00:07:56.000 --> 00:07:59.000
JUST BECAUSE WE'RE
JUST NUTS ABOUT EACH OTHER,

00:07:59.000 --> 00:08:02.000
AND I THINK
THE KIDS SEE THAT,
AND HOPEFULLY--

00:08:02.000 --> 00:08:05.000
YOU FEEL GUILTY
ABOUT DIVORCE ANYWAY,

00:08:05.000 --> 00:08:08.000
AND YOU THINK,
"HAVE I RUINED THEIR LIVES?"

00:08:08.000 --> 00:08:11.000
AND I HOPE THAT THEY
 CAN SEE, YOU KNOW,

00:08:11.000 --> 00:08:13.000
WHAT A TERRIFIC
 MARRIAGE IS LIKE,

00:08:13.000 --> 00:08:16.000
AND THAT I HOPE
 WE'RE MODELING

00:08:16.000 --> 00:08:18.000
WHAT LOVE IS.

00:08:23.000 --> 00:08:26.000
HAPPILY EVER AFTER--

00:08:26.000 --> 00:08:28.000
I USED TO THINK
OF IT AS AN IDEAL,

00:08:28.000 --> 00:08:31.000
BUT NOW, TO ME,
IT'S JUST REALITY.

00:08:31.000 --> 00:08:33.000
THIS IS
 "HAPPILY EVER AFTER."

