00:11:41.000 --> 00:11:43.000
JOY, WHAT'S IT LIKE
TO BE A STEPPARENT?

00:11:43.000 --> 00:11:44.000
WELL, I'M NOT
A STEPPARENT,

00:11:44.000 --> 00:11:46.000
BUT I'M A PSYCHOLOGIST
WHO DEALS WITH THIS A LOT,

00:11:46.000 --> 00:11:48.000
AS YOU POINT OUT,
STATISTICALLY.

00:11:48.000 --> 00:11:52.000
MY SORT OF RULE OF THUMB,
WHICH I GET ENORMOUS
HASSLE ABOUT,

00:11:52.000 --> 00:11:55.000
IS, AS A STEPPARENT,
YOU CAN BE A GOOD HOST
AND FRIEND, AND THAT'S IT.

00:11:55.000 --> 00:11:58.000
THINK ABOUT THE THINGS
YOU REMEMBER MOST
FROM YOUR CHILDHOOD.

00:11:58.000 --> 00:12:01.000
IT WAS NOT YOUR PARENT
BEING A WARDEN
OR A DISCIPLINARIAN.

00:12:01.000 --> 00:12:04.000
IT WAS GUIDING YOU,
SPENDING TIME WITH YOU,
BEING A FRIEND TO YOU.

00:12:04.000 --> 00:12:06.000
I'M NOT CERTAINLY
SUGGESTING THAT PARENTS

00:12:06.000 --> 00:12:08.000
SHOULDN'T TAKE
RESPONSIBILITY
FOR SETTING STRUCTURE,

00:12:08.000 --> 00:12:10.000
BUT THE DISCIPLINARY
FUNCTION OF PARENT

00:12:10.000 --> 00:12:13.000
HAS TO BE WITH
THE BIOLOGICAL PARENT,
NOT WITH THE STEPPARENT,

00:12:14.000 --> 00:12:16.000
BECAUSE, OTHERWISE,
THE CHILD WILL SAY,
QUITE LEGITIMATELY,

00:12:16.000 --> 00:12:18.000
"YOU'RE NOT MY PARENT."

00:12:18.000 --> 00:12:22.000
WELL, YOUR BRINGING UP
THE ISSUE OF DISCIPLINE
IS THE PROBLEM,

00:12:22.000 --> 00:12:25.000
AND, YET, I THINK IT MAY BE
THAT YOU WISH SO MUCH

00:12:25.000 --> 00:12:27.000
YOU COULD GET CLOSE
TO THAT STEPCHILD

00:12:27.000 --> 00:12:29.000
AND GIVE 'EM WHAT YOU
FEEL LIKE THEY'VE LOST

00:12:29.000 --> 00:12:31.000
WHEN THEIR
REAL PARENT LEFT.

00:12:31.000 --> 00:12:34.000
- WHAT YOU VALUE
  IS THE TIME SPENT.
- SURE.

00:12:34.000 --> 00:12:37.000
YOU, AS A STEPPARENT, CAN
SPEND TIME WITH THAT CHILD

00:12:37.000 --> 00:12:39.000
WITHOUT SAYING:
"HAVE YOU DONE
YOUR HOMEWORK?"

00:12:39.000 --> 00:12:42.000
"FINISH YOUR MEAL,"
"DON'T TALK TO
YOUR MOTHER THAT WAY,"

00:12:42.000 --> 00:12:44.000
"DON'T HIT YOUR
BROTHER OR SISTER."

00:12:44.000 --> 00:12:46.000
AGAIN, I THINK
MOST OF US--

00:12:46.000 --> 00:12:48.000
AND I WOULD CERTAINLY
INCLUDE MYSELF IN THIS--

00:12:48.000 --> 00:12:50.000
CONFUSE THE ROLE
OF PARENT WITH THAT OF

00:12:50.000 --> 00:12:52.000
THE ONE WHO HAS
TO TELL A CHILD

00:12:52.000 --> 00:12:54.000
WHEN THEY'RE
DOING SOMETHING WRONG,
ALMOST EXCLUSIVELY.

00:12:54.000 --> 00:12:57.000
IT SEEMS TO ME THAT
WHEN THEY'RE DOING
SOMETHING RIGHT

00:12:57.000 --> 00:12:59.000
IS WHEN IT
REALLY MATTERS.

00:12:59.000 --> 00:13:02.000
AND I'LL BET THE STEPPARENT
IS ALWAYS FEELING

00:13:02.000 --> 00:13:04.000
A COMPETITIVE FEELING

00:13:04.000 --> 00:13:06.000
FOR THAT PARENT
THAT'S ABSENT,

00:13:06.000 --> 00:13:10.000
AND THE SORT OF GATEKEEPING--
"I'VE GOT TO BE BETTER
THAN THAT PERSON."

00:13:10.000 --> 00:13:14.000
WITH ALL DUE RESPECT,
I THINK THAT'S A VERY
MALE POINT OF VIEW.

00:13:14.000 --> 00:13:16.000
I THINK THAT'S SORT OF
A COMPETITIVE THING,

00:13:16.000 --> 00:13:18.000
IF I SOMEHOW HAVE TO
COMPETE WITH THIS PERSON
WHO'S NOT HERE.

00:13:18.000 --> 00:13:20.000
IT'S NOT COMPETING FOR
THE CHILD'S ATTENTION.

00:13:20.000 --> 00:13:22.000
IT'S COMPETING FOR
THE MOTHER'S ATTENTION--

00:13:22.000 --> 00:13:25.000
"HEY, AM I
A BETTER HUSBAND?"

00:13:25.000 --> 00:13:28.000
I THINK YOU'RE RIGHT.
IT EXISTS, BUT IT'S
MISDIRECTED, IT'S PROJECTED.

00:13:28.000 --> 00:13:31.000
I WONDER IF THERE ISN'T,

00:13:31.000 --> 00:13:34.000
IN THE BACK OF EVERY
STEPPARENT'S MIND,

00:13:34.000 --> 00:13:36.000
"I'M NOT THIS CHILD'S
REAL PARENT.

00:13:36.000 --> 00:13:38.000
I CAN'T REALLY KNOW HER."

00:13:38.000 --> 00:13:42.000
IF I HAD A NICKEL
FOR EVERY PARENT WHO SAID,
"MY KID TELLS ME EVERYTHING,"

00:13:42.000 --> 00:13:45.000
AND THE KID SAYS,
"I DON'T TELL
MY PARENTS ANYTHING--"

00:13:45.000 --> 00:13:47.000
I THINK THAT NOTION

00:13:47.000 --> 00:13:49.000
OF CLOSENESS
AND INTIMACY

00:13:49.000 --> 00:13:51.000
IS SOMEWHAT OF AN ILLUSION
ON THE PARENT'S PART.

00:13:51.000 --> 00:13:55.000
THEREFORE, WE FEEL THAT
THEY'RE A REFLECTION ON US,
WHICH THEY ARE NOT.

00:13:55.000 --> 00:13:57.000
THEY'RE A REFLECTION
ON THEMSELVES.

00:13:57.000 --> 00:13:59.000
IT'S A MUCH MORE LIMITED
AND MUCH MORE PERVASIVE ROLE

00:13:59.000 --> 00:14:01.000
THAN WE THINK
OF IT AS BEING.

00:14:01.000 --> 00:14:04.000
TO BE A GOOD PARENT IS
NOT TO FORM THAT CHILD.

00:14:04.000 --> 00:14:06.000
IT'S TO NURTURE THAT CHILD,
TO LOVE THAT CHILD,

00:14:06.000 --> 00:14:08.000
TO HELP THAT CHILD
FIGURE OUT WHO THEY ARE.

00:14:08.000 --> 00:14:11.000
SO THE ROLE OF STEPPARENT,
WHEN WE GET THAT DEFINITION,

00:14:11.000 --> 00:14:14.000
BECOMES VERY EASY
BECAUSE THE ROLE IS

00:14:14.000 --> 00:14:17.000
TO MAKE THAT CHILD FEEL
WELCOME, WHICH IS A GOOD
HOSTESS OR GOOD HOST,

00:14:17.000 --> 00:14:20.000
AND TO FEEL VALUABLE,
WHICH IS A GOOD FRIEND.

00:14:20.000 --> 00:14:22.000
BUT STILL,
PARENTS SAY TO ME,

00:14:23.000 --> 00:14:25.000
"I WANT TO LOVE
HER AS MUCH

00:14:25.000 --> 00:14:27.000
AS I DO
MY OWN CHILDREN."

00:14:27.000 --> 00:14:30.000
THAT DRIVES ME CRAZY,
LIKE SOMEHOW YOU COULD
MEASURE LOVE ON A SCALE.

00:14:30.000 --> 00:14:32.000
WE DON'T LOVE
OUR CHILDREN THE SAME.

00:14:32.000 --> 00:14:34.000
WE DON'T LOVE
TWO CHILDREN THE SAME.

00:14:34.000 --> 00:14:38.000
WE MAY LOVE THEM
THE SAME, WHATEVER
THAT MESSY WORD MEANS.

00:14:38.000 --> 00:14:41.000
WE DON'T FEEL THE SAME
ABOUT OUR BOY CHILDREN
AND OUR GIRL CHILDREN.

00:14:41.000 --> 00:14:43.000
WE DON'T FEEL THE SAME
WAY ABOUT OUR OLDEST
AND OUR YOUNGEST.

00:14:43.000 --> 00:14:45.000
WHY SHOULD WE
FEEL THE SAME ABOUT
ANY TWO HUMAN BEINGS?

00:14:45.000 --> 00:14:47.000
I THINK THAT'S
A MISTAKEN NOTION.

00:14:47.000 --> 00:14:49.000
WE GET VERY GOOEY
WITH THAT "L" WORD.

00:14:49.000 --> 00:14:52.000
IN OTHER WORDS,
YOU'RE SAYING,
"DON'T TRY SO HARD

00:14:52.000 --> 00:14:55.000
TO BE THE SAME
WITH YOUR OWN CHILDREN
AND STEPCHILDREN."

00:14:56.000 --> 00:14:59.000
I'M SAYING BE THE BEST
PERSON YOU CAN BE

00:14:59.000 --> 00:15:02.000
TO EVERYBODY YOU RUN INTO,
INCLUDING THOSE
IN YOUR HOUSEHOLD.

00:15:03.000 --> 00:15:05.000
THAT'S VERY FEMALE.

00:15:05.000 --> 00:15:08.000
- WELL, THAT'S BECAUSE
  IT'S BRILLIANT.
- I SEE.

