YOU ARE VULNERABLE.
YOU'D LIKE TO PROTECT THEM

00:19:34.000 --> 00:19:36.000
FROM THE FACT THAT
THEY'RE DIFFERENT

00:19:36.000 --> 00:19:39.000
FROM KIDS WHO HAD
THEIR OWN PARENTS.

00:19:39.000 --> 00:19:41.000
IS THAT RIGHT?

00:19:41.000 --> 00:19:43.000
YES, OF COURSE.

00:19:43.000 --> 00:19:46.000
ANY PARENT, I GUESS,
WANTS TO PROTECT
THEIR CHILD.

00:19:46.000 --> 00:19:48.000
YOU SAID SOMETHING
VERY INTERESTING.

00:19:48.000 --> 00:19:51.000
YOU WANTED TO MAKE
THE DIFFERENCES IMPORTANT,

00:19:51.000 --> 00:19:53.000
AND THAT'S TRUE,

00:19:53.000 --> 00:19:55.000
BUT IT'S NOT
 GOING TO WORK.

00:19:55.000 --> 00:19:59.000
SHE'S STILL GOING TO COME
TO YOU FOR BEING TEASED,
FOR BEING DIFFERENT.

00:19:59.000 --> 00:20:02.000
WHAT YOU HAVE TO DO
IS HAVE HANDLED
YOUR OWN FEELINGS

00:20:02.000 --> 00:20:04.000
SO WHEN SHE
COMES TO YOU,

00:20:04.000 --> 00:20:06.000
YOU'RE READY
TO HELP HER WITH HERS.

00:20:06.000 --> 00:20:09.000
AND IT'S BOUND TO HAPPEN.

00:20:09.000 --> 00:20:12.000
ONE THING I'D LIKE
TO URGE YOU TO DO

00:20:12.000 --> 00:20:15.000
IS LET HER KNOW
SOME CHINESE ADULTS

00:20:15.000 --> 00:20:17.000
SO SHE CAN IDENTIFY
WITH THEM.

